Thesis (Accompanies Model 4):

Defense is a significant factor in a teams success in the NBA, and players like Kawhi Leonard and Lebron James are praised as being dynamic two-way players, but defensive effects can be challenging to quantify. The average distance of the closest defender on shots will have a negative relationship with the shooting teams margin of victory, particularly in close games decided by ten points or less.
